    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nMissing buffer line, duplicated line below after placing virtual line above a folded line.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.fn.setline(1, vim.fn.range(1, 6) )\nvim.cmd('2,3fold')\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'v', function()\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, 1, 0, 0, { virt_lines = {{{'virt_below'}}}})\nend)\n```\n\n1. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n2. Type <kbd>v</kbd>, observe missing line 5, duplicate line 6. \n\nRelated: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33361#issuecomment-2781689543, #33205.\n\nHave been looking into those issues but have yet to find a solution that resolves this properly.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo incorrect display.\n\nResolving this will likely require updating https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ca16b54c866bca6d10fc4f60874e6469bd0751cd/test/functional/ui/decorations_spec.lua#L2904-L2914, which contains an incorrect screen state.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-102+gca16b54c86\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1283\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
